<br>
&quot;You feel vulnerable&quot;<br>
&quot;You feel adhere to the ground&quot;<br>
&quot;You feel drowsy&quot;<br>
<br>
Ok...first was Malisement (checked the &quot;buff&quot;-description)<br>
second was some kind of root/snare<br>
Third ...well drowsy.<br>
<br>
Ok root and drowsynes didnt cause any trouble and were gone fast after battle.<br>
But Malisement was there for quite a while.<br>
I also mentioned that my &quot;arch shielding&quot; buff was gone. <br>
so I tried to recast arch shielding:<br>
&quot;You begin casting Arch Shielding.&quot;<br>
&quot;Your spell did not take hold.&quot;<br>
<br>
repeated...same result.<br>
<br>
(I had following effects on me at that time: Levitate, Jboots, Phantom armor and Malisement)<br>
As soon as Malisement was gone I could cast arch shielding as usual.<br>
<br>
Now either I'm a very bad Mage or that seems strange to me...<br>
I always thought malisement &quot;just&quot; decreases resistances (and yeah...my resistances were decreasd big time ;-) ) but doesnt have any dispell effect.<br>
<br>
So why did it <br>
1) probably overwrite my arch Shielding (cannot really see it in the logs, snce there was no &quot;You feel less armored&quot; message)<br>
2) disable the ability to recast arch Shielding on myself. Of course....when it really overwrites AS then I wont be able to cast it as long as the effect is on me...But is Malisement supposed to do so? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170427" target="_blank">
